This was a bug found by nimbus. Verify and fix: F-002 · 🟡 medium · logic: Policy derivation poller can be left running after status changes away from policy_pending, causing extra GET /api/reviews requests during later review phases.
Fix: Tighten the dependency array and guards for the policy_pending polling effect so it only depends on stable identifiers and status, not on the refreshCycle it mutates. For example:

useEffect(() => {
  if (!review || review.status !== 'policy_pending') {
    return;
  }
  const timer = window.setTimeout(() => {
    setRefreshCycle((value) => value + 1);
  }, 2000);
  return () => {
    window.clearTimeout(timer);
  };
}, [review?.id, review?.status]);
This ensures that when the review transitions to policy_ready/queued/running, the effect is torn down and no new timers are scheduled. Also consider the same pattern for the policyProgressCycle effect (depending only on status and maybe reviewId).

